# CASSANDRA System Context

## Product
- CASSANDRA is a collective premonition platform: users submit dreams/premonitions, AI analyzes signals, system matches with real-world events, verified matches affect user rating/role.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript (`strict: true`)
- Supabase (Auth, Postgres, RLS, Realtime, Storage)
- Tailwind + PostCSS
- `next-intl` (`ru`/`en`, messages in `messages/ru.json`, `messages/en.json`)
- Anthropic Claude (`@anthropic-ai/sdk`)
- `react-simple-maps` + `d3-scale`, `date-fns`
- Vercel + cron routes from `vercel.json`

## Routing and i18n
- UI routes are under `src/app/[locale]/...`.
- Use locale-aware navigation helpers from `src/navigation.ts`.
- In client components, use `Link` and `useRouter` from `@/navigation` (not `next/navigation` for app links).

## Middleware
- `src/middleware.ts` combines:
  - Supabase session/auth redirects via `src/lib/supabase/middleware.ts`
  - `next-intl/middleware` locale handling
- Redirect rules:
  - unauthenticated + non-public/non-api -> `/login`
  - authenticated on `/login` or `/register` -> `/feed`

## Supabase clients
- Client components: `src/lib/supabase/client.ts`
- Server components/route handlers: `src/lib/supabase/server.ts`
- Cron/background routes use service-role access.

## Key known issues (always consider)
1) `entries.type` constraint mismatch (`dream|premonition` in migrations vs code using `unknown`).
2) Code uses `entries.ip_country_code`, `entries.ip_geography`, `entries.is_quarantine`; verify columns exist in real DB.
3) `verification/index.ts` may still contain legacy join assumptions (`profiles` vs `users`) in some branches.
4) Tailwind custom tokens/animations must exist in `tailwind.config.ts` when referenced in UI.
5) Avoid hardcoded RU strings in UI; prefer `next-intl`.
6) Analyze race risk: immediate `/api/analyze` call plus cron.

## Coding rules for this project
- Keep TypeScript strict and explicit.
- Prefer existing project architecture and APIs over introducing parallel patterns.
- Keep UI text translatable (`useTranslations` / `getTranslations`).
- Respect locale-aware routing and auth flow in middleware.
- Validate DB/schema assumptions before changing data-flow logic.

